============================================================================
UI STYLING & STYLESHEET PROTOCOL (CRITICAL FOR STRATEGY BUILDER)
============================================================================
UI_STYLING_RULES = """
CENTRAL STYLESHEET ENFORCEMENT - ALL UI COMPONENTS

CRITICAL RULE: NO HARDCODED STYLES ANYWHERE IN DEVELOPMENT CODE

AUTHORITY: src/strategy_builder/ui/styles.py is the ONLY source of truth
for all UI styling, colors, spacing, typography, and visual design.

MANDATORY PROTOCOL:

1️⃣ STYLESHEET IMPORTS (REQUIRED IN EVERY UI FILE)
   ✓ from src.strategy_builder.ui.styles import [class/constant]
   ✓ Never import inline styles
   ✓ Never use style dictionaries in component files
   ✓ Never hardcode colors, fonts, sizes, spacing
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT):
   from src.strategy_builder.ui.styles import (
       PRIMARY_COLOR, SPACING_UNIT, BUTTON_STYLE, CARD_STYLE
   )

2️⃣ STYLE APPLICATION (MANDATORY PATTERN)
   ✓ All components use styles.py definitions
   ✓ Dynamic styling: reference style constants
   ✓ Conditional styling: use style helper functions from styles.py
   ✓ Custom styling: ONLY add to styles.py, NEVER in component
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT):
   class StrategyCard(QWidget):
       def __init__(self):
           self.setStyleSheet(CARD_STYLE)
           self.main_layout.setSpacing(SPACING_UNIT * 2)
           self.button.setStyleSheet(BUTTON_STYLE)
   
   EXAMPLE (WRONG):
   class StrategyCard(QWidget):
       def __init__(self):
           self.setStyleSheet("background: white; padding: 10px;")
           self.button.setStyleSheet("color: #007ACC; font-size: 14px;")

3️⃣ COLOR USAGE (CENTRALIZED ONLY)
   ✓ Define all colors in src/strategy_builder/ui/styles.py
   ✓ Reference via COLOR_NAME constant
   ✓ NEVER hardcode hex colors, RGB, or color names in components
   ✓ NEVER use inline color definitions
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in styles.py):
   PRIMARY_COLOR = "#007ACC"
   SECONDARY_COLOR = "#F3F3F3"
   SUCCESS_COLOR = "#28A745"
   ERROR_COLOR = "#DC3545"
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in component):
   button.setStyleSheet(f"background-color: {PRIMARY_COLOR};")
   
   EXAMPLE (WRONG - hardcoded):
   button.setStyleSheet("background-color: #007ACC;")

4️⃣ SPACING & SIZING (CENTRALIZED ONLY)
   ✓ Define all spacing/sizing in styles.py
   ✓ Use SPACING_UNIT as base unit
   ✓ Use SIZE_* constants for dimensions
   ✓ NEVER hardcode pixel values in components
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in styles.py):
   SPACING_UNIT = 8
   BUTTON_HEIGHT = SPACING_UNIT * 5  # 40px
   CARD_PADDING = SPACING_UNIT * 2    # 16px
   FONT_SIZE_BASE = 14
   FONT_SIZE_LARGE = 16
   FONT_SIZE_SMALL = 12
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in component):
   layout.setSpacing(SPACING_UNIT)
   layout.setContentsMargins(CARD_PADDING, CARD_PADDING, CARD_PADDING, CARD_PADDING)
   button.setMinimumHeight(BUTTON_HEIGHT)
   
   EXAMPLE (WRONG - hardcoded):
   layout.setSpacing(8)
   layout.setContentsMargins(16, 16, 16, 16)
   button.setMinimumHeight(40)

5️⃣ TYPOGRAPHY (CENTRALIZED ONLY)
   ✓ Define all fonts in styles.py
   ✓ Use FONT_* constants for family, size, weight
   ✓ NEVER hardcode font definitions in components
   ✓ NEVER inline QFont() creation
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in styles.py):
   FONT_FAMILY = "Segoe UI"
   FONT_SIZE_BASE = 14
   FONT_SIZE_HEADING = 18
   FONT_WEIGHT_NORMAL = 400
   FONT_WEIGHT_BOLD = 600
   
   def create_font(size=FONT_SIZE_BASE, bold=False):
       font = QFont(FONT_FAMILY, size)
       if bold:
           font.setWeight(FONT_WEIGHT_BOLD)
       return font
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT - in component):
   from src.strategy_builder.ui.styles import create_font, FONT_SIZE_HEADING
   label.setFont(create_font(FONT_SIZE_HEADING, bold=True))
   
   EXAMPLE (WRONG - hardcoded):
   font = QFont("Segoe UI", 18)
   font.setBold(True)
   label.setFont(font)

6️⃣ THEME CONSISTENCY (MANDATORY)
   ✓ All components must use styles.py for visual consistency
   ✓ Theme changes only in styles.py
   ✓ No per-component styling overrides
   ✓ Global theme changes automatically affect all components
   
   WORKFLOW:
   1. User requests color change
   2. Update ONLY in src/strategy_builder/ui/styles.py
   3. All components using that style automatically update
   4. No component files modified
   5. ZERO hardcoded styles anywhere

7️⃣ ENFORCEMENT CHECKLIST (BEFORE EVERY COMMIT)
   ☐ No hardcoded color hex values in any component file
   ☐ No inline setStyleSheet() with style definitions
   ☐ No hardcoded pixel values for spacing/sizing
   ☐ No inline QFont() creation (use styles.py helper)
   ☐ No style dictionaries in component code
   ☐ All color refs use COLOR_* constants from styles.py
   ☐ All spacing refs use SPACING_* constants from styles.py
   ☐ All font refs use create_font() from styles.py
   ☐ styles.py is ONLY file with hardcoded style values
   ☐ All UI files import from styles.py
   
   COMMAND TO CHECK:
   grep -r "setStyleSheet\|QFont\|#[0-9A-Fa-f]\|padding:\|margin:\|color:" \
       src/strategy_builder/ui/*.py \
       --include="*.py" --exclude="styles.py" | wc -l
   
   Result should be: 0 (no matches except in styles.py)

8️⃣ EXCEPTION HANDLING
   ✓ ONLY exception: styles.py can have hardcoded values
   ✓ NEVER: Any other file has hardcoded styles
   ✓ If component needs new style:
     1. Add to styles.py first
     2. Then use in component
     3. NEVER add directly to component
   
   EXAMPLE (CORRECT WORKFLOW):
   Requirement: "Make button text bold and blue"
   
   Step 1 - Add to styles.py:
   BOLD_BUTTON_STYLE = "font-weight: 600; color: #007ACC;"
   
   Step 2 - Use in component:
   from src.strategy_builder.ui.styles import BOLD_BUTTON_STYLE
   self.button.setStyleSheet(BOLD_BUTTON_STYLE)
   
   EXAMPLE (WRONG WORKFLOW):
   Requirement: "Make button text bold and blue"
   
   ❌ WRONG - add directly to component:
   self.button.setStyleSheet("font-weight: 600; color: #007ACC;")

9️⃣ SCALABILITY & MAINTAINABILITY
   ✓ Single source of truth: styles.py
   ✓ Global theme changes: Edit styles.py only
   ✓ No style duplication across components
   ✓ Easy to implement dark mode (swap COLORS dict)
   ✓ Easy to implement responsive design (adjust SPACING_UNIT)
   ✓ Easy to audit styles (all in one file)
   ✓ Easy to maintain consistency (automatic across all components)

🔟 VIOLATIONS & CORRECTIONS
   
   VIOLATION DETECTION:
   - Hardcoded color in component → RED FLAG
   - Inline style dictionary → RED FLAG
   - Direct pixel value in component → RED FLAG
   - New QFont() in component → RED FLAG
   - setStyleSheet() with definitions in component → RED FLAG
   
   CORRECTION PATTERN:
   1. Identify violation (grep search above)
   2. Extract style to styles.py
   3. Replace with constant reference
   4. Test visual consistency
   5. Commit only styles.py changes for that fix

FULL DETAILS: CLINE_INSTITUTIONAL_RULES.md → UI_STYLING_PROTOCOL

COMMAND TO VERIFY COMPLIANCE:
# All style definitions should be in styles.py only
grep -r "background-color:\|color:\|padding:\|margin:\|font-weight:" \
    src/strategy_builder/ui/ --include="*.py" | grep -v "styles.py" | wc -l
# Result must be: 0

STYLE EXTENSIONS WORKFLOW:
1. User requests new styling
2. Add to src/strategy_builder/ui/styles.py
3. Export constant or helper function
4. Import in component
5. Use exported style
6. Zero changes to component files
"""

